[4]
Date: Wed 12 Sep 2007
Source: DEFRA, FMD Key Current Information [edited]
<http://www.defra.gov.uk/footandmouth/>

On 12 Sep 2007 FMD was confirmed at a farm in
Surrey. The farm comprises a number of separate
parcels of land: a single Protection Zone has
been put in place extending 3 km [1.86 miles]
around each of them, with a Surveillance Zone of
10 km [6.2 mile] radius beyond that. Footpaths
are being closed in the Protection Zone. Cattle
on the affected farm are being culled, together
with animals on an adjacent farm.
A national movement ban -- affecting cattle,
sheep, pigs and other ruminants -- has been
imposed throughout England, and parallel
arrangements are being made by the Scottish and
Welsh administrations. No movements of
susceptible animals are allowed except under
licence; some licences have now been made
available, however licence conditions may vary
between England, Scotland and Wales. All farms --
particularly those in the Protection and
Surveillance Zones -- must implement increased biosecurity.
A Temporary Control Zone has been placed around a
premises in Dereham, Norfolk. This is a
precautionary measure. An assessment of clinical
symptoms by Animal Health veterinary staff has
been carried out, and laboratory test results are awaited.
--
